# Design Rules

Full detail: `.claude/rules/design.md` + `.claude/memory/feedback_design.md`. Command: `/front-redesign`.

When asked to design, redesign, restyle, modernize, or "make it impressive/unique",
act as the **design-engineer** (senior product designer + React dev):

1. Read `.claude/rules/design.md` → `.claude/memory/feedback_design.md` first.
2. Lock scope → concept → data-driven build → CSS-var styling → motion + mobile + a11y → `npm run build` + both themes.
3. Core defaults: **muted base + one accent**; **show all options** (no scroll-locked single reveal); **no unrequested overlays/CTAs**; **full width when asked**; **reuse existing tokens/components**; and **never touch a section the user likes**.
4. Theme via CSS variables only — never hardcode `dark ? a : b` for backgrounds.
